The paper deals with the problem of 3D human shape estimation from single RGB images, which is a topic that falls under computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also mentions the use of convolutional neural networks, which is a common technique in computer graphics (cs.GR). The use of depth maps and volumetric representations also suggests that the paper could be categorized under multimedia (cs.MM). The paper also mentions the use of a discriminator in an adversarial fashion, which is a technique commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper proposes a non-parametric approach for 3D shape estimation, which is a topic that falls under artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
